A Navy Commander has been abducted by gunmen suspected to be kidnappers in Ondo State. The Naval Officer whose identity is yet to be ascertained was abducted along Ose/Oba Akoko, Akoko North East Local Government in the Northern Senatorial District of the state. He was said to be traveling to Abuja when the gunmen emerged from the bush and waylaid his vehicle. The military officerâ€™s abduction comes a few days after an Army Captain was also snatched while traveling from Abuja within the same axis The kidnappers were said to have made contact with the family, demanding N50 million ransom. Meanwhile, a military and police joint rescue team are already combing the bushes around the area of the incident in a bid to rescue the victim. According to sources, the Commanding Officer of 323 Artillery Brigade Command in Ondo State had visited the scene of the incident to assess the situation. Confirming the incident, the Police Public Relations Officer, PPRO, Ondo, State Command, ASP Tee-Leo Ikoro said various tactical squads have been deployed to man the area. He explained that the police have sought the support of the host communities in a bid to checkmate and curtail crime on the said road. These content links are provided by Content.ad. Both Content.ad and the web site upon which the links are displayed may receive compensation when readers click on these links. Some of the content you are redirected to may be sponsored content. View our privacy policy here. To learn how you can use Content.ad to drive visitors to your content or add this service to your site, please contact us at info@content.ad. Family-Friendly Content Only recommend family-friendly content Website owners select the type of content that appears in our units. However, if you would like to ensure that Content.ad always displays family-friendly content on this device, regardless of what site you are on, check the option below. Learn More